@francisco_yira Oh, no. Those instructions are actually way too complicated, you'll have to repeat them each time you upgrade #RStats, and they even break your R installation ("… delete Sys.getenv(“R_USER”) [in C:\Program Files\R\R-4.0.0\library\base\R\Rprofile]"). Instead, …   

1/

@francisco_yira That will cause #RStats 4.1.* to install to:

C:/RFolder/R/x86_64-w64-mingw32-library/4.1

and when you upgrade to R 4.2.0 later, it'll automagically install to:

C:/RFolder/R/x86_64-w64-mingw32-library/4.2

3/

@francisco_yira To have #RStats install your packages under, say, C:/RFolder/ on MS Windows, add the following as-is to your personal ~/.Renviron file:

R_LIBS_USER="C:/RFolder/R/%p-library/%v"

e.g. via:

cat('R_LIBS_USER="C:/RFolder/R/%p-library/%v"\n', append = TRUE, file = "~/.Renviron")
